title.value: A neutron spin-echo study of the dynamics of block copolymer micellesin liquid and gel phases

abstract.value: Neutron spin echo will be used to investigate chain dynamics in micelles formed by a diblock copolymer in water. The system was previously studied on IN11 and a two-mode model of the dynamics was used to fit the data (Castelletto et al. HCP 119, 8158, 2003). Due to the limited range of timescales available (up to around 20 ns in our experiments), it was not possible to distinguish between the dynamics in solution and gel phases. This will be investigated using IN15, where measurements up to 200 ns are possible. The neutron spin-echo measurements will be complemented by dynamic light scattering, which will cover the range from 100 ns - 1s.
